_sText:
From imagination to art.

A year ago, I wanted to create the best map i can, so I started making bhop_shutdown. As you may know, it had a lot of problems and overall was not a great map, however I tried my best and personally think that it was quite successful. Now I tried my best again and made maybe not the best, but surely a great map that i can be proud of. Shutdown2 is a sequel to the first shutdown - same concept of flybhop/surf combined map with intentional skips and simple strafe elements that is fun and more or less easy on both auto and scroll, yet very hard to run.

This map tells you a story about how an idea is born in a creator's mind and what the creator has to face throughout developing his idea. As a contradiction to the first shutdown, it is set in a world that is being developed from scratch. 

Gameplay-wise, I have tried to improve wherever i could to make the map more fun to run and play casually. It has a lot of surfs and spins so I should probably say sorry to people with low sens, haha.

I used a lot of assets in this map - comment for credit if i forgot you.

Music:

By Soda (not the aus one) and Nallieheai.

Map is now updated. Thanks to everyone who played it. I did not change the name so server owners will have to replace the original map and also wipe the bonus times

This is my biggest creation so far. I started working on this map last fall. It was supposed to be a big collaboration but things did not really work out. I stopped working on it after January and it just lied around purposelessly on my PC. Recently i finished it - and here it is. Aesthetics inspired (stolen) by badg3s and epiphany.

This map combines in itself an autobhop and a scroll gameplay routes - every of the 3 kz parts is skippable on auto for interesting gameplay.

The map also has a small lore where everything blacks out as you progress through it, like a world that is destroyed as you move on through it - nothing deep, but whatever. Don't forget about stupid 7 seconds strafe bonus tho! Best part, honestly.

Known issues: 
Due to the way i made soundscapes, on big servers, although it is very unlikely, player that chooses not to play music still can start hearing it if another player flagged as music_on enters a trigger at the same time.
There is also some weird issues about momentum mod not letting you on the map if you place the start zone. Literally have nfi why that happens as everything works fine in css.

All music by me - https://soundcloud.com/sodxwxter

Special thanks are listed - sorry to everyone who i forgot about. People who wanted to collaborate and who helped - you are awesome.

Copy paste from first version

Hello all!
So I started making this map about 2 months ago with many great ideas, i worked pretty much 10-12 hours a day on it as this map has been one of my best creations so far!
However, I ran into the Hammer limitation wall a few houndred times and coulden't make the map as I wished to, I've probbably deleted and skipped out on about 10 lvls that I'm probbably gonna create another map for btw! but i'm still pretty happy with the result and it's still in beta so I might remove some of this with some of the other ideas.

The map now has 7 levels, pretty hard, long levels. Well some are not that long but fairly hard.
It's not an impossible map to finnish, but the avrage bhopper is going to need alot of time finnishing it.
Also some of the lvls are anti-script (yay!) where you'll need precission jumps, not long speedy jumps.
And it's also not a map you'll speed throug in 20 min.
Theres 5 soundscapes for 5 of the levels, acctually it's just ambient sounds that plays in the entire map when a new level is reached.
and note ***I DO NOT OWN THESE SONGS, THEY WILL BE REPLACED/REMOVED AT REQUEST OF OWNER***
thoug I found it a little hard contacting the people that created final fantasty to ask for their permission to use them, shoulden't be a problem as I bought the cds anyway :P
But yeah as you might have guessed, it's going from relaxing to really chaotic music in the final level!

Also a big shoutout to silent assasin who were kind enough to let me use his design for the finnish room and help me along the way making my very first bhop map! lu <3

And I belive that is all I got to say!
It's still in beta, stuffs gonna change definitivly so please leave a feedback :)

Oh also, it's multi jump on the platforms, no func_doors!


Changes - 
Map optimized to the max, sound files optimized (the quality acctually turned out pretty bad i'll see what i can do about that but it's only playing once every time the map is on and a player reaches a new level so it's not that much of a deal now.
The filesize is cut to half and players should no longer experience any lagg inside now!

bhop_scrollmore is a linear map for EZ-Mode/auto, ironic!

no multi triggers, the fastest hopper wins.

the pink blocks designate the pathway for the normal timer
the turquoise blocks signify the bonus route possibilities

the green block area is the start zone and the red being the end zone.

while making this map i kept in mind the open style of very old bhop maps, open skybox, its just something I wanted to incorporate into a newer modern style looking map

This map is another linear map made by Jake™ #usa (me)
If you fall, you're going back to the start. (take your time)

- The zone underlined in green is the Start Zone
- The Red room in the middle of the map is the End Zone
- The Turquoise represent the Bonus, the illusionary !b is the beginning platform.

No multi-triggers, the fastest bhopper wins the race.
Enjoy and remember to Auto on ;)
